<p>I have a problem with sass concatenating the elements. I want to obtain -webkit-calc to be written together like this : </p>  <pre><code>width: -webkit-calc(100% - 6rem); width: -moz-calc(100% - 6rem); width: -o-calc(100% - 6rem); </code></pre>  <p>Sass code:</p>  <pre><code>$vendorlist: unquote("-webkit-") unquote("-moz-") unquote("-o-"); @mixin calcmixx($prop, $val) { #{$prop}: calc(#{$val}); @each $pref in $vendorlist {     #{$prop}:#{$pre} + calc(#{$val});   } } </code></pre>  <p>Here is the method used to include the mixin in sass file:</p>  <pre><code>.PromoTitle{ margin: 0 auto; @include calcmixx( width, '100% - 6rem'); </code></pre>  <p>CSS result:</p>  <pre><code>.PromoTitle{     width: calc(100% - 6rem);     width: -webkit- +calc(100% - 6rem);     width: -moz- +calc(100% - 6rem);     width: -o- +calc(100% - 6rem);} </code></pre>  <p>If I try to write without "+"</p>  <pre><code>   #{$prop}:#{$pref} calc(#{$val}); </code></pre>  <p>This is the result:</p>  <pre><code>width: calc(100% - 6rem); width: -webkit- calc(100% - 6rem); width: -moz- calc(100% - 6rem); width: -o- calc(100% - 6rem); </code></pre>  <p>And is I write it in this way there will be no result:</p>  <pre><code>#{$prop}:#{$pref}calc(#{$val}); </code></pre>